Detailed Description

Class which contains information about an object on the map. The MapObjectInfo may either be added to an OverlayItem onto the map, or it may represent a map object, integrated into the map (such as a street).

Member Typedef Documentation

typedef wf_int32 WFAPI::MapObjectInfo::map_object_info_t

The type of map object info.

A set of predefined constants exists, but it is also allowed to add more types if needed.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum WFAPI::MapObjectInfo::idType

The type of ID that is used, integer key, or string. Either may be used, depending on what is most appropriate. ID_KEY is recommended to use if possible to avoid extra allocations.

Enumerator:
ID_KEY  An integer based id-type.
ID_STRING  A string based id-type.
